Day 5 and only another 2 days until I have been on this yoga journey for a week, and I am really enjoying my time, even if I am still struggling with the poses as we move along but I am not giving up, I am going to continue all the way through.  I have gotten myself into a good routine of finding 30 minutes in my quiet day to do these classes, and although I struggle through, at the end I am happy I stayed with the session to the very end.  It is so easy to give up when you don't have the flexibility or you can not do downward dog but who knows, the next step could be something you can do and this is my journey through this revolution.  I can't reach to the mat and I am not as flexible as Adriene but I am working at my own level, and trying whatever is put in front of me ...  I am treating these session as if I am in an actual yoga class and if I was in a class, I wouldn't walk out because I can't do a pose, and so I have myself in a good place with a routine that is working for me ...

This feels like a journey of Eat, Pray, Love ,,, and at the moment this is Pray, where I honour myself, be true to myself and find my inner self through commitment, pride and wellbeing.  Commitment, in staying on this path to the very end. Pride, where I am amazed with what I am capable of doing and Wellbeing, giving myself the time to heal and improve through adapting a healthy lifestyle.

I know that in all likelihood no one will get to the end of this comment because it's way too long, but dammit, I'm posting it anyway! 

I was a pretty dedicated yogi up until several months ago (moving a few times and setback from mental health issues made things difficult) so when I saw that Adriene was doing yet another of her awesome 30 (or 31 in this case) day programs I knew that it would be the perfect kick to get back on the mat in a meaningful way.  I was a day behind as I started January 2nd (I won't get into the very inexcusable reasons why I wasn't on my mat for the 1st, but I'm sure you can imagine) and as I did Day 4 first thing this morning I figured I'd try to catch up and do Day 5 this evening as well. 

I really just wanted to say that I can't believe the difference between this morning's practice and Day 5's! It could just have something to do with the fact that I have more energy in the evenings generally, but I felt so much more in tune with myself with this practice. I was having more fun, wasn't internally yearning for a child's pose, and felt myself flowing through the vinyasas almost effortlessly--I almost felt like my old practicing self again! I know I still have a long way to go before I'm back to where I was, but this has me eager to continue with the 31 days because I know how much better I'm going to feel about myself at the end of it--in mind, body, and consciousness. 

Anyway, all this to say thank you, Adriene!
